on, R.P., Ayres, M.P., Flannigan, M.D., Hanson, P.J., Wotton, B.M., Climate change and forest disturbances (2001) Bioscience, 51, pp. 723-734; Dovciak, M., Hrivnak, R., Ujhazy, K., Gomory, D., Seed rain and environmental controls on invasion of Picea abies into grassland (2008) Plant Ecol, 194, pp. 135-148; Greene, D.F., Johnson, E.A., Tree recruitment from burn edges (2000) Can J For Res, 30, pp. 1264-1274; Greene, D.F., Noel, J., Bergeron, Y., Rousseau, M., Gauthier, S., Recruitment of Picea mariana, Pinus banksiana, and Populus tremuloides across a burn severity gradient following wildfire in the southern boreal forest of Quebec (2004) Can J For Res, 34, pp. 1845-1857; Greene, D.F., Macdonald, S.E., Cumming, S., Swift, L., Seedbed variation from the interior through the edge of a large wildfire in Alberta (2005) Can J For Res, 35, pp. 1640-1647; Greene, D.F., Macdonald, S.E., Haeussler, S., Domenicano, S., Noel, J., Jayen, K., Charron, I., Swift, L., The reduction of organic-layer depth by wildfire in the North American boreal forest and its effect on tree recruitment by seed (2007) Can J For Res, 37, pp. 1012-1023; Habrouk, A., Retana, J., Espelta, J.M., Role of heat tolerance and cone protection of seeds in the response of three pine species to wildfires (1999) Plant Ecol, 145, pp. 91-99; Hancock, M.H., Summers, R.W., Amphlett, A., Willi, J., Testing prescribed fire as a tool to promote Scots pine Pinus sylvestris regeneration (2009) Eur J For Res, 128, pp. 319-333; Hanssen, K.H., Natural regeneration of Picea abies on small clear-cuts in SE Norway (2003) For Ecol Manag, 180, pp. 199-213; Henig-Sever, N., Poliakov, D., Broza, M., A novel method for estimation of wild fire intensity based on ash pH and soil microarthropod community (2001) Pedobiologia, 45, pp. 98-106; (2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, , IPCC, Geneva: WMO; Jayen, K., Leduc, A., Bergeron, Y., Effect of fire severity on regeneration success in the boreal forest of northwest Qu